# API Integration Patterns

**Backend**: NestJS 11 Backend API 
**Client**: Axios with interceptors 
**Pattern**: Service Layer → Hook → Component

## Architecture Overview

```
Component
    ↓ uses
Custom Hook (useBooks, useBorrows)
    ↓ calls
Service Layer (bookService, borrowService)
    ↓ uses
HTTP Client (apiRequest with interceptors)
    ↓ sends
HTTP Request to Backend API
```

**Key Principle**: Each layer has single responsibility. Components don't call API directly.

---

## Pattern 1: Service Layer Structure

**Location**: `src/core/services/api/*.service.ts`

**Purpose**: Centralized API calls with type safety

**Structure**:

```typescript
// src/core/services/api/books.service.ts
import { apiRequest } from './client';
import type { Book, BookFilters } from './types/book.types';
import type { ApiResponse, PaginatedResponse } from './types/api-response';

export const bookService = {
  /**
   * Get paginated list of books
   */
  async getAll(filters?: BookFilters): Promise<PaginatedResponse<Book>> {
    const params = {
      page: filters?.page || 1,
      per_page: filters?.perPage || 20,
      search: filters?.search,
      sort_field: filters?.sortField,
      sort_direction: filters?.sortDirection,
    };
    
    const response = await apiRequest.get<PaginatedResponse<Book>>(
      '/books',
      { params }
    );
    
    return response.data;
  },

  /**
   * Get single book by ID
   */
  async getById(id: string): Promise<Book> {
    const response = await apiRequest.get<{ book: Book }>(`/books/${id}`);
    return response.data.book;
  },

  /**
   * Create new book (admin/librarian only)
   */
  async create(data: CreateBookDTO): Promise<Book> {
    const response = await apiRequest.post<{ book: Book }>('/books', data);
    return response.data.book;
  },

  /**
   * Update existing book
   */
  async update(id: string, data: UpdateBookDTO): Promise<Book> {
    const response = await apiRequest.put<{ book: Book }>(
      `/books/${id}`,
      data
    );
    return response.data.book;
  },

  /**
   * Delete book
   */
  async delete(id: string): Promise<void> {
    await apiRequest.delete(`/books/${id}`);
  },
};
```

**Best Practices**:
- ✅ One service per resource (books, users, borrows)
- ✅ JSDoc comments for all methods
- ✅ Fully typed params and return values
- ✅ Use `apiRequest` helper (has interceptors)
- ✅ Transform backend response to frontend types if needed
- ❌ Don't add business logic (belongs in hooks)
- ❌ Don't manage loading/error state (belongs in hooks)

