## Pattern 7: Request Cancellation

**Problem**: Component unmounts but API request continues

**Solution**: Cancel requests on unmount

**Implementation**:

```typescript
import { useEffect, useRef } from 'react';
import axios from 'axios';

const useBooks = () => {
  const abortControllerRef = useRef<AbortController>();
  
  useEffect(() => {
    const fetchBooks = async () => {
      // Create new AbortController
      abortControllerRef.current = new AbortController();
      
      try {
        const response = await apiRequest.get('/books', {
          signal: abortControllerRef.current.signal,
        });
        setBooks(response.data);
      } catch (error) {
        if (axios.isCancel(error)) {
          console.log('Request canceled');
        } else {
          setError(error);
        }
      }
    };
    
    fetchBooks();
    
    // Cleanup: cancel request on unmount
    return () => {
      abortControllerRef.current?.abort();
    };
  }, []);
};
```

**When to Use**:
- ✅ Slow API calls (search, filters)
- ✅ Components that mount/unmount frequently
- ✅ Tab switching, route changes
- ❌ Critical writes (may cause partial updates)

