## Pattern 8: Retry Logic

**Problem**: Transient network errors should retry

**Solution**: Retry with exponential backoff

**Implementation**:

```typescript
const retryRequest = async <T>(
  fn: () => Promise<T>,
  maxRetries = 3,
  delay = 1000
): Promise<T> => {
  for (let i = 0; i < maxRetries; i++) {
    try {
      return await fn();
    } catch (error) {
      if (i === maxRetries - 1) throw error;
      
      // Exponential backoff
      await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, delay * Math.pow(2, i)));
    }
  }
  throw new Error('Max retries exceeded');
};

// Usage
const books = await retryRequest(() => bookService.getAll());
```

**When to Use**:
- ✅ Network errors (timeout, connection refused)
- ✅ 502/503 server errors (temporary)
- ❌ 4xx client errors (won't succeed on retry)
- ❌ Authentication errors (need user action)

